<subSubSection id="73FB72F0CE4C124D3D44FAC3FDD4FCB6" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4C124F3D44FAC3FE4BFAF8" blockId="16.[264,1015,1256,1317]" box="[264,421,1291,1317]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
(
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE4C124F3D5DFAC3FE73FAF8" box="[273,413,1291,1317]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–34" captionStartId="17.[264,382,1825,1849]" captionTargetBox="[411,1159,599,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-169@17.[407,1179,597,1821]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 32–34. Chrysotimus ningxianus sp. nov. (male). 32. Apical half of wing; 33. first flagellomere, lateral view; 34. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048669/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs. 32–34</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4C124F3D44FA86FEB6FA65" blockId="16.[264,1324,1358,1904]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis. First flagellomere subtriangular, as long as wide. Hind tarsomere 1 with 2 sparse black bristles at base and row of 7–8 pv. Epandrium with 2 finger­like lateral processes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4C124F3D74FA0EFBE6FA3D" blockId="16.[264,1324,1358,1904]" box="[312,1032,1478,1504]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Description. 
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE4C124F3D83FA0EFDFBFA3D" bold="true" box="[463,533,1478,1504]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="FC198C9ECE4C124F3EF8FA0EFCFFFA3D" box="[692,785,1478,1504]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="FC198C9ECE4C124F3FE3FA0EFBE6FA3D" box="[943,1032,1478,1504]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4C124F3D74FA26FC70F975" blockId="16.[264,1324,1358,1904]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; frons and face brilliant. Hairs and bristles on head yellow. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 2 very long oc and 2 very short posterior hairs. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE4C124F3D86F9F6FDCCF985" box="[458,546,1598,1624]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–34" captionStartId="17.[264,382,1825,1849]" captionTargetBox="[411,1159,599,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-169@17.[407,1179,597,1821]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 32–34. Chrysotimus ningxianus sp. nov. (male). 32. Apical half of wing; 33. first flagellomere, lateral view; 34. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048669/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) brown; first flagellomere subtriangular, about as long as wide; arista dorsal, brown, with short pubescence. Proboscis brown, with brownish hairs; palpus yellow, with yellow hairs and 2 brownish apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4C124E3D74F97EFEDAFDFB" blockId="16.[264,1324,1358,1904]" lastBlockId="17.[264,1325,284,550]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Thorax metallic green with gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on thorax yellow; 6 dc, 9– 10 irregularly paired acr short and hair­like; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles. Propleuron with 1 yellow hair and 1 yellow bristle on lower portion. Legs [fore tarsomeres 3–5 broken] yellow, with mid and hind tarsomere 5 brown. Hairs and bristles on legs yellow; coxae with yellow hairs and bristles; fore coxa with 3–4 anterior and apical bristles, mid coxa with 3 anterior bristles, hind coxa with 1 brownish outer bristle near middle. Mid femur with 1 av and 1 pv apically, hind femur with 1 av apically. Mid tibia with 2 ad and 2 pd; hind tibia with 2 ad, 2 pd, and 3–4 pv on apical half. Fore tarsomere 1 with row of about 10 v; mid tarsomere 1 with row of 7–8 v; hind tarsomere 1 just with 2 sparse black ventral bristles at base and row of 7–8 pv. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres of legs LI 3.2: 1.8: 0.7:?:?:?; LII 4.2: 2.3: 0.9: 0.6: 0.4: 0.4; LIII 5.0: 1.6: 1.0: 0.7: 0.5: 0.5.</paragraph>
<caption id="6F9E71F3CE4D124E3D44F8E9FCD5F886" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048669" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5048669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048669/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" startId="17.[264,382,1825,1849]" targetBox="[411,1159,599,1797]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4D124E3D44F8E9FCD5F886" blockId="17.[264,1323,1825,1883]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE4D124E3D44F8E9FE3AF8E4" bold="true" box="[264,468,1825,1849]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">FIGURES 32–34.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FCE15AF8CE4D124E3DACF8EAFD06F8E4" authority="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[480,744,1826,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ningxianus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE4D124E3DACF8EAFD06F8E4" box="[480,744,1826,1849]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Chrysotimus ningxianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="12A64012CE4D124E3EB8F8E9FCA3F8E5" box="[756,845,1825,1848]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 32. Apical half of wing; 33. first flagellomere, lateral view; 34. genitalia, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4E124D3D74FED4FCC8FEBE" blockId="18.[264,1323,284,875]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Wing hyaline (
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE4E124D3DA8FED4FDD5FEEB" box="[484,571,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–34" captionStartId="17.[264,382,1825,1849]" captionTargetBox="[411,1159,599,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-169@17.[407,1179,597,1821]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 32–34. Chrysotimus ningxianus sp. nov. (male). 32. Apical half of wing; 33. first flagellomere, lateral view; 34. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048669/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
), veins brownish; R 
<subScript id="A765233ECE4E124D3F6FFEEFFCA9FEE1" attach="left" box="[803,839,295,316]" fontSize="9" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">4+5</subScript>
and M parallel apically, CuAx ratio 0.21. Squama yellow with pale hairs. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4E124D3D74FEB9FEDCFE6E" blockId="18.[264,1323,284,875]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Abdomen metallic green with pale gray pollen. Hairs and bristles on abdomen brownish.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4E124D3D74FE09FDE2FDF6" blockId="18.[264,1323,284,875]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE4E124D3DB5FE09FDBBFE06" box="[505,597,449,475]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–34" captionStartId="17.[264,382,1825,1849]" captionTargetBox="[411,1159,599,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-169@17.[407,1179,597,1821]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 32–34. Chrysotimus ningxianus sp. nov. (male). 32. Apical half of wing; 33. first flagellomere, lateral view; 34. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048669/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Epandrium distinctly longer than wide, somewhat square, apically with 2 finger­like lateral processes; surstylus slender, apically with bristles; cercus long, with broad base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4E124D3D74FDF1FDF6FD8E" blockId="18.[264,1323,284,875]" box="[312,536,569,595]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE4E124D3D74FDA9FAC5FDA6" blockId="18.[264,1323,284,875]" box="[312,1323,609,635]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
